<br>
* Enchanters<br>
Fun in grind groups, they are the crowd control and the folks that level them know this and enjoy this aspect.  They are part of the holy trinity and have a great usefulness in such groups.  And in low numbers, are useful as buffers and crowd control on alot of raids.  But as the number of enchanters increase, their fun level and such exponentially decrease in a high end guild situation.  Their nuke power is horribly below all under casters, so the extra's can't feel anymore useful.<br>
<br>
* Necromancers<br>
Origianlly the ultimate caster.  Everyone and their dog had a necromancer twink.  Good in everything, master in none.  Sort of the bard of casters.  While they have continued to grow in this area, it has only been a PvP wise advancement.  While their PvE has greatly decreased compared to other casters.  In grind groups they are valuable and have lots of abilities if the groups take advantage of them.  In a raid situation they become a mana battery and not much beyond this due to their lack of arsenal.  Plus with lousy pathing and limitations, pets are generally considered unuseful on raids.  <br>
<br>
* Magicians<br>
A Great class in all respect.  They are very useful in a grind group when a group knows their potential.  A good mage is a huge asset to a group while a idiot is a huge liability.  With damage shields, mod rods, pet, and good nukes; they have the capability of adding value to any group.  But many people don't realize their true potential and as such would take a druid or a wizard over a magician in alot of situations.  On raids, mages are the most boring of a class.  They become rod whores.  Everyone wants their rods.  They lose alot of desirability to play due to not really doing anything different but dropping rods in the high end game.  <br>
<br>
* Wizards<br>
The constant talkers, they don't shut up.  Wanting ultimate power, but always getting moldy cookies.  Their solo ability is probably the best of all pure casters in the high end game.  Their AE group ability has great potential beyond the VI nerfs.  In a normal group they are rather a boring class.  With the holy trinity they are stuck to sitting on their arses and doing far less damage then they thought they should be capable of.  In a raid situation, wizards are the highlight of the casters.  Magicians, Enchanters, and Necromancers envy their power to do damage and only have wet dreams of matching them.  Other caster jobs are to support the wizard along with the raid. <br>
<br>
That is my basic summary of the pure casters.  Now what can be done to help balance these classes, both playwise and funwise.<br>
<br>
All Casters:<br>
* Allow DD's and DoT's that can't be stacked with the same spell from another caster the ability to stack.<br>
* Allow Caster shield buff line the ability to Stack with Shaman Focus line<br>
<br>
Enchanters:<br>
* Give them nukes that rival that of Magicians in their current state.  While in grind groups they are crowd control, on raids they could do more damage.<br>
<br>
Necromancers:<br>
* Give them the ability to take control of their pet as a first person.  With the variety of pets, they would add a whole new level of strategy to the necromancer.  Plus with several classes to play, it would rarely get boring.  Also this would make pets more useful in raid situations.<br>
* Give them a better ability to Resurrect Players<br>
* Give them a upgraded Mez ability, so that they could be considered a better crowd control member in a grind group.  <br>
<br>
Magicians:<br>
* Give them the innate spell debuff that wizards have.  So they could hit mobs as effectively.  With their less efficient spells, this really wouldn't infringe on wizard territory.<br>
* Give them a lure line of spells.  Or a Lure spell.  In the current state of the game and resist rates on mobs.  This would not be an unbalancing or bad approach on wizard territory again.  This would only increase their usefulness and fun factor on raids by allow them to do more then drop rods. <br>
* Give them some ability to Evac the group to the safe spot, high level.  Or atleast a means to *TL* members to the safe spot. <br>
<br>
Wizards:<br>
* God only knows...We are fuggered<br>
* Read Graffe's! Plenty of Ideas.<br>
* And Yes I am a wizard<br>
