<br>
I agree.<br>
<br>
Keep the mezzes short &amp; expensive.  Toss in interesting side effects, like a mez that costs the necro HP, or lifetaps HPs from the mob and gives it to the necro.  Give them all long recast times, and keep the duration short -- force a necro to give up some spell slots to do mezzing effectively.  Allow any mez to overwrite a necro mez. . .<br>
<br>
For example, give a necro a 1.0 CT 12.0 RCT mez, 5 mana, does 200 damage to the necro and mezes for 24 seconds (damage only done if mez lands).  Or, a 3.0 CT 8.0 RCT 150 mana mez, drains 100 HP &amp; gives it to the necro, mezzes for 24 seconds.<br>
<br>
Mages:<br>
Targettable summon spells.<br>
<br>
Target a player, have the summoned item appear in the target's inventory.<br>
<br>
Add charged LORE NO DROP right-click summoned items.  Wizard only evak or nuke or deaggro items.  Enchanter only PBAE mez or stun or self-rune clickies.  And the like.<br>
<br>
It is an entire world of effects you could add that wouldn't infringe on anything.  Being targetted &amp; NO DROP/LORE, it is alot more dynamic than stacking mod rods on the ground.<br>
