Seems to me someone who plays an enchanter and doesn't like doing that stuff is pretty silly.  That's like saying &quot;who'd want to play a Warrior if all they do is hit stuff and taunt!?!?&quot;  That's THE CLASS, there wasn't any secret about it.  Enchanters nuke too much already in my book, like Clerics. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 620<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/02 2:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: =)</span><hr size=1> Excluding Kunark and old world zones, one possible solution would be to have manaburn have ZERO delay between recasts.  Being fully OOM after using it once gives us the need to sit down and med up again anyway.  The only problem with this is the pathetic 32k HP mobs from Kunark(including Venril Sathir in this).  So, get rid of the delay between manaburns, and we would probably be well balanced.<br>
<br>
Putting damage bonuses to our spells based on our intelligence, or having the mana cost be lower based on intelligence, and total mana pool might also help.<br>
<br>
Really, we suffer the most because stats don't affect individual spell damage output.  A level 60 wizard with sunstrike does IDENTICAL damage per cast to any other wizard with sunstrike(since summoned focus items are pretty much identical to the effect on items).<br>
