<br>
In a single exp group or on a fast moving crowd control raid I have neither space nor mana nor inclination to mem any booms and only the speicifically needed debuffing dots.  But when dealing with non mezzable zones (Kael etc) or the &quot;what crowds?&quot; boss mob, it woudl be nice to be more than wasted space.  After an enchanter for KEI/shiss and a second as backup we could be better replaced by any other class at that level.  Its at that point that enchanters start cussing out verant for leaving them nothing to do with their mana.<br>
<br>
So sure, I want a better boom.  Something that has better mana efficiency than 250 mana for 650 damage landing one in 5 casts and not landing at all since by cast attempt 4 the super high taunt has me aggroed and dead.   I dont need a scad of lines of booms, I *don't* want to be a better boomer than mages druids or wizzies, I just want some way to spend my mana on offense not defense.   My greatest fear is that Verant in caster balancing will look at the enchanters and say &quot;Balanced, no probs&quot; or worse yet &quot;not balanced, lets give the whores more buffs to make all the *other* players happy with&quot;..<br>
