 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/02 8:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mage perspective</span><hr size=1> First, the recent pet changes have really increased the ability of magicians to contribute to raid damage. Pet &quot;problems&quot; are about 85-90% reduced with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and new pet coding measures, and the other 10-15% can usually be avoided by careful paying of attention. So basically, even on nasty multi-mob raids, I can send in a pet to attack and watch it out of the corner of my eye while I drop a few mod rods for the healers. And if I can't devote enough time to watching the pet, I can tell it to hold and have 100% guarantee that it will sit there until I tell it to do something else or it dies.<br>
<br>
Still, I suggest the following be taken into consideration:<br>
<br>
*) In Jewish mythology, a golem was an animated being constructed from the powers of earth, wind, fire, and water. Given that magicians are nominally masters of those four elements, it would seem appropriate that magicians could also have some line of spells for controlling these beings. If magicians deserve some kind of bane spell, and if the devs don't want it to be too horribly unbalanced, then some form of golem-bane would be appropriate. It would give magicians a new little niche to play with, and it would add some roleplay value (yeah, not a big issue I realize, but still).<br>
<br>
*) Barring that, stretch the definition a bit and consider various golems and constructs as summoned beings and give the versus-summon spells a lower resist rate, including golems currently immune or nearly so to magic attacks (spite golems, black reavers, etc.)<br>
<br>
*) Consider some form of pet-only weapon with a low-resist proc or high ATK and combat stats specifically for designated uber encounters. Make the summoned items zonebound (similar to PoA keys...rentable but not zoneable) and make the spells castable only in certain designated zones such as Kael or Skyshrine. The weapons could also be tagged only for a specific mob model (such as Giant) so as not to give magicians in, say, Velketors Labyrinth any advantage with the spiders and gargoyles when the weapon was only intended to contribute to the Velketor battle itself. This would help magicians better utilize pets on large raids without throwing typical game balance askew. The spells don't have to be common, they can be quested similar to wizard bane spells. Heck, they can even use a fairly costly reagent. The goal is just to give pets (all pets) an edge where they need it most: making physical contact with level 61+ mobs.<br>
<br>
